// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// SCENE B1 — SPIRIT OF NICOLA PISANO
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

title: talk_nicola
position: 300,300
group: nicola
color: blue
actor: SENIOR_M
---
<<if not $talked_to_francesco>>
    The spirits of the quarry are not yet ready to speak.
    Go find Francesco first.
    <<target npc_francesco>>
<<elseif $piece_nicola>>
    Well done! You already have my piece.
    Go find the other spirits.
<<else>>
    I am Nicola Pisano, a medieval sculptor.
    It was the year 1260 when I first came here.
    <<card pisano_Card>>
    I chose this marble for the Baptistery of Pisa.
    But before making art... you need to extract the marble!
    Let me explain how it has been done through the centuries.
    <<jump nicola_explain_techniques>>
<<endif>>
===

title: nicola_explain_techniques
position: 450,300
group: nicola
color: blue
actor: SENIOR_M
---
First technique: the wooden wedge.
The Romans pushed fig-wood wedges into cracks in the rock.
<<card cava_romana_Card>>
Then they soaked the wood — as it swelled, it split the stone!
Clever, wasn't it?
<<jump nicola_technique_2>>
===

title: nicola_technique_2
position: 450,400
group: nicola
color: blue
actor: SENIOR_M
---
Second technique: explosives.
<<card esplosivi_cave_Card>>
From 1600 onwards, workers used gunpowder in the quarries.
They blasted the mountainside to break off the blocks.
It was fast, but it destroyed a lot of marble.
And the damage to the environment was enormous.
<<jump nicola_technique_3>>
===

title: nicola_technique_3
position: 450,500
group: nicola
color: blue
actor: SENIOR_M
---
Third technique: the diamond wire.
<<card macchinari_moderni_Card>>
Since 1970, a steel wire coated in industrial diamonds has been used.
It cuts the rock with perfect precision and no waste.
In one day, you can cut what once took three whole months!
Now tell me: can you match each technique to the right era?
<<jump nicola_activity_intro>>
===

title: nicola_activity_intro
position: 600,300
group: nicola
color: purple
actor: SENIOR_M
---
Match each technique to its correct era.
You can do it!
<<activity match_the_technique nicola_activity_result normal>>
===

