title: talk_michelangelo
position: 300,600
group: michelangelo
color: blue
actor: SENIOR_M
---
<<if not $talked_to_francesco>>
    The spirits of the quarry are not yet ready to speak.
    Go find Francesco first.
    <<target npc_francesco>>
<<elseif $piece_michelangelo>>
    You already have my piece. Good!
    Go find the other spirit.
<<else>>
    I am Michelangelo Buonarroti.
    Perhaps the greatest sculptor who ever lived.
    <<card michelangelo_Card>>
    I came to Carrara in person to choose my blocks.
    I spent eight months in these quarries just for the Tomb of Julius II.
    I trusted no one else to choose the marble for me.
    <<jump michelangelo_explain_sculpture>>
<<endif>>
===

title: michelangelo_explain_sculpture
position: 450,600
group: michelangelo
color: blue
actor: SENIOR_M
---
Marble is not just a rock.
It is the most living material in existence.
The sculpture is already inside the block.
My work is to remove the excess marble and set it free.
With this marble I carved the Pieta, the David and the Moses.
Works that will last for thousands of years.
<<jump michelangelo_explain_lizzatura>>
===

title: michelangelo_explain_lizzatura
position: 450,700
group: michelangelo
color: blue
actor: SENIOR_M
---
<<card lizzatura_Card>>
But do you know how the marble reached Florence or Rome?
These blocks weigh as much as ten cars.
There were no trucks, no trains.
They used the lizzatura: a wooden sled called a lizza.
The quarrymen slid it down incredibly steep slopes.
They controlled the speed using thick hemp ropes.
It was the most dangerous job that existed.
Many quarrymen lost their lives doing it.
Now I ask you to draw what you have learned.
<<jump michelangelo_activity_intro>>
===

title: michelangelo_activity_intro
position: 600,600
group: michelangelo
color: purple
actor: SENIOR_M
---
Draw the lizza on the canvas.
Show me you understood!
<<activity canvas_michelangelo michelangelo_activity_result normal>>
===

