title: talk_bernini
position: 300,900
group: bernini
color: blue
actor: ADULT_M
---
<<if not $talked_to_francesco>>
    The spirits of the quarry are not yet ready to speak.
    Go find Francesco first.
    <<target npc_francesco>>
<<elseif $piece_bernini>>
    You already have my piece! Well done, young artist.
    Go back to Francesco now.
<<else>>
    I am Gian Lorenzo Bernini!
    Sculptor, architect, painter.
    I changed the way marble was used forever.
    <<card apollo_e_dafne_bernini_Card>>
    Look at Apollo and Daphne — I carved it between 1622 and 1625.
    I was only twenty-three years old when I began!
    <<jump bernini_explain_apollo>>
<<endif>>
===

title: bernini_explain_apollo
position: 450,900
group: bernini
color: blue
actor: ADULT_M
---
This sculpture captures the exact moment Daphne transforms into a laurel tree.
Her fingers become branches, her feet roots, her skin bark.
All of this in marble — a rock as hard as iron!
No one before me had dared to attempt such a thing.
People believed marble could never look soft.
I proved them wrong.
<<jump bernini_explain_wire>>
===

title: bernini_explain_wire
position: 450,1000
group: bernini
color: blue
actor: ADULT_M
---
<<card macchinari_moderni_Card>>
In my time, marble was cut with chisels and mallets.
Every millimetre was sweat and effort.
Today there is the diamond wire: a steel wire coated in industrial diamonds.
It runs at hundreds of metres per minute.
It slices through marble like butter, with no waste at all.
In a single day you can do the work that in my time took three months.
I wish I had had such a tool!
But enough talking — put my sculpture back together!
<<jump bernini_activity_intro>>
===

title: bernini_activity_intro
position: 600,900
group: bernini
color: purple
actor: ADULT_M
---
Reassemble the pieces of Apollo and Daphne.
Four pieces. You can do it!
<<activity berninijigsaw bernini_activity_result normal>>
===

